## ğŸ¯ Key Concepts Explained

### 1. **The PEMA Brand (Physical Core)**
-   **Product**: A proprietary, knowledge-based **silver clay**.
-   **IP**: Advanced formulation and **laser-based mold-making** techniques.
-   **Innovation**: The **Smart Coin** project (hollow, NFC-enabled collectible).

### 2. **The Super Platform (Digital Ecosystem)**
-   **Education Platform**: Courses on using PEMA products, evolving into a marketplace for creators.
-   **Marketplace**: A Web3-enabled platform for selling crafts, with NFT-based authenticity.
-   **Customer Equity Model**: Every purchase converts a portion of the profit into equity (shares) for the customer.

### 3. **The Meta-Strategy (The "Why")**
-   **Networked Architecture**: The ecosystem is composed of "islands" (specialized services) connected via a central "interaction hub."
-   **Open Knowledge**: This entire repository is a living Wiki that evolves with the business.
-   **AI-Augmented**: We leverage AI across all functions to accelerate design, content creation, and strategic planning.

---

## âš¡ Quick Start Guide

### Prerequisites
- **Rust** 1.75+
- **Node.js** 20+ & **pnpm** 8+
- **Docker** & **Docker Compose**

### Setup & Run
```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/pema-project/pema-ecosystem.git
cd pema-ecosystem

# 2. Copy the environment template
cp .env.example .env.local
# (Edit .env.local with your settings)

# 3. Start local infrastructure (Postgres, Redis, Kafka)
cd infra/docker && docker-compose up -d && cd ../..

# 4. Build and run the project
# This command will use Turborepo to build all packages and start the apps.
pnpm install
pnpm run dev
```
The application will be available at `http://localhost:3000`.

